<subSubSection id="9DD81BD5F2EC13F36F55A71276B1A5DE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="ABB4954A56CDD66E11628D6CCBEE1FCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EFFDF9C91EACC37B6543ACF29FFE1B4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="34C769D1E428574271817CDBB2548BA2" authorityName="X. Aubriot &amp; S. Knapp" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum sulawesi" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sulawesi">
<emphasis id="EFC770F61680381D8D88757E5500A1D2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum sulawesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named for the island on which it appears to be endemic, Sulawesi, which is of an extraordinary composite geologic nature at the collision zone of the Asian, Pacific, and Australian tectonic plates (
<bibRefCitation id="B7949B26A118B40A72DDF2084484572E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s005310100228" author="Villeneuve, M" journalOrPublisher="International Journal of Earth Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="524 - 537" refId="B257" refString="Villeneuve, M, Gunawan, W, Cornee, JJ, Vidal, O, 2002. Geology of the central Sulawesi belt (eastern Indonesia); constraints for geodynamic models. International Journal of Earth Sciences 91 (3): 524 - 537, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s005310100228" title="Geology of the central Sulawesi belt (eastern Indonesia); constraints for geodynamic models." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s005310100228" volume="91" year="2002">Villeneuve et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="49F572681E5C1DBDFCBC96F96046071E" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.198.79514.figure70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/689763" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 70" startId="F70">
